    "recap_url": "https://www.LibertyFlames.com/news/2026/3/22/baseball-kennesaw-state-rallies-for-4-3-win-over-liberty-in-series-finale",
    "recap_headline": "",
    "recap_text": "KENNESAW, GA. \u2013\nThe Kennesaw State Owls scored two in the eighth to tie and won the game on a two-out single in the ninth inning to salvage the final game of their three-game series with the Liberty Flames 4-3 at Mickey Dunn Stadium on Sunday.\nLiberty took the first two games of the series 2-0 in 10 innings on Friday and 11-5 on Saturday.\nThe Flames built a 3-1 advantage behind starting pitcher\nBradley Zayac\nthrough the first seven innings, before the Owls' comeback.\nShortstop\nTanner Marsh\nhad two hits in the game, while designated hitter\nJordan Jaffe\ncollected two hits and scored a run for Liberty.\nRight fielder Landon Scilly hit his first home run of the season in the sixth inning for the Flames.\nLiberty drops to 3-3 in CUSA play and 15-8 overall. Kennesaw State moves to 2-4 in CUSA and 10-10 overall.\nBox Score Highlights\nRecords:\nLiberty (15-8, 3-3 CUSA); Kennesaw State (10-10, 2-4 CUSA)\nLocation:\nMickey Dunn Stadium (Kennesaw, Ga.)\nWP:\nDaniel Powell (4-1) |\nLP:\nJosh Swink\n(1-2)\nScoring Summary\n1\nst\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Sorenson doubles, Jaffe scores, 1-0\n2\nnd\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 DeCandido walks, Swofford scores, 2-0\n2\nnd\n\u2013 KSU \u2013 Posey singles, Williams scores, 2-1\n6\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Scilley homers, 3-1\n8\nth\n\u2013 KSU \u2013 Williams doubles,\u00a0 Chirrello and McGee score, 3-3\n9\nth\n\u2013 KSU Alig singles, Cole scores, 4-3\nNotable Numbers\n- Kennesaw State held a 12-7 advantage in hits over Liberty. Neither team committed an error.\n- The Flames left eight men on base. The Owls left nine men on base.\n- Zayac allowed one run on eight hits over 6 2/3 innings. He struck out two and did not walk a batter.\n-\nJosh Swink\n, who took over for Zayac, takes the loss. The left-hander gave up three runs on three hits over 1 2/3 innings. He struck out two and walked two.\n- Kennesaw State reliever Daniel Powell records the win. He allowed one run on three hits over 5 1/3 innings. The third reliever to pitch for the Owls, the right-hander struck out four and walked one.\n- Three Kennesaw State hitters had two hits apiece in the game, led by third baseman Connor Williams, who also drove in two runs and scored one.\nBeyond the Box Score\n- Liberty takes the series 2-1 for its first CUSA series win of the season.\n- The Flames are 6-3 on the road in 2026.\n- With two singles in the game, Marsh collects his team-leading ninth multi-hit game of the season. The shortstop led the Flames in multi-hit games last year.\n- Jaffe records his sixth multi-hit game. The designated hitter has at least one hit in eight of the last nine games.\n- Zayac has pitched six or more innings in each of his last three starts.\nUp Next\nLiberty returns home to start a four-game homestand. The Flames will begin the homestand by hosting the UNCG Spartans on Tuesday. Game time at Worthington Stadium is scheduled for 4 p.m.\nThat ball is high! It is far! It is........GONE!\nLandon Scilley\nHome Run!\npic.twitter.com/JDSXtbCiqe\n\u2014 Liberty Baseball (@LibertyBaseball)\nMarch 22, 2026",
